- Yes. Just like the word.

244
00:14:57,900 --> 00:15:01,400
The names... Are you good with names?

245
00:15:01,430 --> 00:15:03,930
I'm not. So, I have a trick.

246
00:15:03,930 --> 00:15:07,980
- What is it?
- I imagine the names on their foreheads.

247
00:15:07,980 --> 00:15:09,060
- Really?
- Yes.

248
00:15:09,060 --> 00:15:12,010
It's easy if you picture that.

249
00:15:12,010 --> 00:15:15,010
Gyu Ri. Wu Yeol.

250
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:18,200
I'll try writing your names, too.

251
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:20,900
- I'm not good at it, either.
- Really?

252
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:24,200
- Memorize it. Min Ju.
- I'll try.

253
00:15:24,230 --> 00:15:27,280
He's acting differently since Gyu Ri came.

254
00:15:28,940 --> 00:15:34,050
I thought that he was masculine.

255
00:15:34,950 --> 00:15:39,100
He was quiet and seemed full of thoughts.

256
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:41,600
He seemed reserved.

257
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:49,000
But I think I like the flashier type.

258
00:15:49,030 --> 00:15:51,970
Someone with stronger eyes, too.

259
00:15:51,970 --> 00:15:54,530
Have you eaten?

260
00:15:54,530 --> 00:15:55,640
[Staring]

261
00:15:55,640 --> 00:15:58,690
He's staring at her.

262
00:15:58,690 --> 00:16:04,080
But his eyes were a bit...

263
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:07,180
I haven't eaten anything.

264
00:16:07,180 --> 00:16:08,930
Yesterday... Yesterday...

265
00:16:08,930 --> 00:16:11,410
Is this a weird thing to ask?

266
00:16:11,410 --> 00:16:13,320
- He's only looking at her.
- You ate yesterday, right?

267
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:15,970
- Of course.
- You had dinner, right?

268
00:16:21,340 --> 00:16:24,730
He was kind of staring at me.

269
00:16:24,730 --> 00:16:28,590
