- I know.

549
00:32:36,760 --> 00:32:39,890
You think she'd get hurt easily.

550
00:32:39,890 --> 00:32:43,840
The second tenant, Gyu Ri, seems most sensitive.

551
00:32:43,840 --> 00:32:46,880
She's like a glass flower. So delicate.

552
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:49,400
She had the most eye movements.

553
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:51,400
She was so nervous.

554
00:32:51,400 --> 00:32:55,500
Kim Seong Min. As he joined,
they started laughing more.

555
00:32:55,510 --> 00:32:57,430
They started talking.

556
00:32:57,500 --> 00:33:00,400
- They brightened up.
- He's chill and kind.

557
00:33:00,430 --> 00:33:03,540
I'm worried he'd end up becoming their counselor.

558
00:33:03,540 --> 00:33:04,930
Me, too.

559
00:33:04,930 --> 00:33:10,650
Putting people at ease isn't
an advantage in that situation.

560
00:33:10,650 --> 00:33:12,310
Kim Seo Won. He was the first.

561
00:33:12,310 --> 00:33:16,000
He walked past people and looked around first.

562
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:17,500
That's not common.

563
00:33:17,500 --> 00:33:20,700
They say, "Did you look around?"
But he looked on his own.

564
00:33:20,700 --> 00:33:24,800
And when Yu Gyeong came last,
his face totally changed.

565
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:28,200
- I think he's transparent.
- Transparent.

566
00:33:28,230 --> 00:33:31,150
Kang Yu Gyeong. She had the best impression.

567
00:33:31,150 --> 00:33:33,700
She's the prettiest woman I've ever seen.

568
00:33:33,700 --> 00:33:35,460
Except for my wife.

569
00:33:35,460 --> 00:33:36,800
On Heart Signal?

570
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:38,970
- She's the most beautiful.
- Including the celebrities?

571
00:33:38,970 --> 00:33:41,330
Including them.

572
00:33:41,330 --> 00:33:43,750
- Really?
- I'm so curious.

573
00:33:43,750 --> 00:33:45,220
Yu Gyeong is powerful.

574
00:33:45,220 --> 00:33:47,020
I'm curious what their occupations are.

575
00:33:47,020 --> 00:33:49,420
I know. What do they do?

576
00:33:51,070 --> 00:33:53,100
Did you look around yet?

577
00:33:53,100 --> 00:33:54,590
Should we look around?

578
00:33:54,590 --> 00:33:57,450
- Sounds good.
- I'd love to.

579
00:33:57,450 --> 00:34:00,700
They'll be living here for a month.

580
00:34:01,680 --> 00:34:04,020
So nice.

581
00:34:04,020 --> 00:34:06,300
[A place with unfamiliar feelings]

582
00:34:06,300 --> 00:34:08,430
[The fifth Signal House]

583
00:34:08,430 --> 00:34:09,760
There's a garden, too.

584
00:34:09,760 --> 00:34:11,510
What? Whoa...

585
00:34:11,510 --> 00:34:12,660
It's huge.

586
00:34:12,660 --> 00:34:14,620
- It's so nice.
- I was surprised, too.

587
00:34:14,620 --> 00:34:15,860
So nice.

588
00:34:15,860 --> 00:34:17,870
This is crazy.

589
00:34:19,720 --> 00:34:22,660
- There's outdoor space.
- You can go out.

590
00:34:22,660 --> 00:34:25,130
What's out there?

591
00:34:25,130 --> 00:34:28,210
I thought it was a pool for a moment.

592
00:34:28,210 --> 00:34:30,290
[Self Talk room]

593
00:34:30,290 --> 00:34:32,100
- What's that?
- I wonder.

594
00:34:32,100 --> 00:34:34,770
Only one person can sit there.

595
00:34:35,900 --> 00:34:39,500
- Here's the kitchen.
- A lot will happen in this kitchen.

596
00:34:39,550 --> 00:34:41,100
This must be our debit card.

597
00:34:41,100 --> 00:34:43,960
- Is it?
- Don't you think? Maybe.

598
00:34:43,960 --> 00:34:45,800
[Grocery card]

599
00:34:45,800 --> 00:34:47,840
So cute. Piggy.

600
00:34:47,840 --> 00:34:50,420
So nice. It's so nice.

601
00:34:50,420 --> 00:34:52,490
The second floor.

602
00:34:52,490 --> 00:34:54,680
[The second-floor living room]

603
00:34:54,680 --> 00:34:56,830
I wish this were my house.

604
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:04,590
Look at those. Dubai chocolate cookies.

605
00:35:05,800 --> 00:35:08,970
- We talked about them earlier.
- Right? They caught my eye.

606
00:35:08,970 --> 00:35:11,580
This looks like the women's room.

607
00:35:11,580 --> 00:35:14,350
[A space with warm and cozy decor]

608
00:35:14,350 --> 00:35:16,370
- Wow.
- So pretty.

609
00:35:16,370 --> 00:35:18,790
- It's so pretty.
- It really is.

610
00:35:18,800 --> 00:35:21,500
- It's so nice.
- The smell.

611
00:35:21,500 --> 00:35:24,030
- Nice, right?
- I'll sleep well.

612
00:35:24,030 --> 00:35:26,710
We haven't looked here, right?

613
00:35:26,710 --> 00:35:28,610
They must be pajamas. They're so cute.

614
00:35:28,610 --> 00:35:30,160
- I have that one.
- I have a pink one.

615
00:35:30,160 --> 00:35:32,300
- I brought mine.
- Me, too.

616
00:35:32,300 --> 00:35:35,300
- This must be the men's room.
- Feels so different.

617
00:35:35,300 --> 00:35:37,280
- It smells so nice.
- So nice.

618
00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:39,930
The men's room is so cool.

619
00:35:39,930 --> 00:35:41,800
I feel like I need to do something.

620
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:44,180
[It makes you want to do something]

621
00:35:44,180 --> 00:35:46,020
So nice.

622
00:35:46,020 --> 00:35:47,820
[Men's room 2]

623
00:35:47,820 --> 00:35:50,240
Both of the rooms are nice.

624
00:35:50,240 --> 00:35:53,840
- I'd want to hurry back home.
- It's so nice.

625
00:35:53,840 --> 00:35:55,300
[Found something]

626
00:35:56,030 --> 00:35:59,770
[Tea room]

627
00:35:59,770 --> 00:36:02,690
We'll drink tea and coffee here.

628
00:36:02,690 --> 00:36:07,030
It feels so oriental.

629
00:36:07,030 --> 00:36:09,050
That's so pretty.

630
00:36:09,050 --> 00:36:10,320
So nice.

631
00:36:10,320 --> 00:36:11,690
Wow.

632
00:36:11,690 --> 00:36:13,860
[A private room with an oriental theme]

633
00:36:13,900 --> 00:36:16,600
Should we check out the third floor?

634
00:36:16,600 --> 00:36:19,470
This is the terrace.

635
00:36:19,470 --> 00:36:21,820
It'd be nice when it snows.

636
00:36:21,820 --> 00:36:23,880
I hope it does.

637
00:36:23,880 --> 00:36:25,260
The view is amazing.

638
00:36:25,260 --> 00:36:27,620
Wow. We're spending a month here?

639
00:36:27,620 --> 00:36:29,360
[Itaewon's sky]

640
00:36:29,750 --> 00:36:32,260
- It's so crazy.
- How many rooms are there?

641
00:36:32,260 --> 00:36:33,690
So pretty.

642
00:36:33,700 --> 00:36:40,300
I noticed a note about 1:1 chats
earlier on the table.

643
00:36:40,300 --> 00:36:42,410
Should we settle this?

644
00:36:42,410 --> 00:36:44,370
- Sounds good.
- 1:1.

645
00:36:44,370 --> 00:36:47,560
Do we get to talk to everyone once?

646
00:36:47,560 --> 00:36:49,580
I think so.

647
00:36:49,580 --> 00:36:51,510
That's why you set the order.

648
00:36:51,510 --> 00:36:53,600
To choose the location and order.

649
00:36:53,600 --> 00:36:55,890
Oh, you're right.

650
00:36:55,890 --> 00:37:00,930
[Who do they want to talk to first?]

651
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:03,380
- Should we settle it?
- Sounds good.

652
00:37:03,380 --> 00:37:05,200
Rock, paper, scissors.

653
00:37:05,200 --> 00:37:08,190
Rock, paper, scissors. Scissors. Scissors.

654
00:37:08,190 --> 00:37:10,270
[In order of Gyu Ri, Yu Gyeong, and Min Ju]

655
00:37:10,270 --> 00:37:11,740
I choose...

656
00:37:11,740 --> 00:37:14,070
[Torn]

657
00:37:16,910 --> 00:37:19,540
I'm so torn about this.

658
00:37:25,190 --> 00:37:28,190
I choose the one who came last.

659
00:37:28,190 --> 00:37:30,390
The one on the right?

660
00:37:30,390 --> 00:37:33,170
Seo... Seo Won.

661
00:37:33,170 --> 00:37:36,360
I choose Seong Min.

662
00:37:36,360 --> 00:37:40,150
[Yu Gyeong chooses Seong Min]

663
00:37:40,150 --> 00:37:42,600
- Wu Yeol for me.
- Okay.

664
00:37:42,600 --> 00:37:48,200
Then, as for space, have the men...

665
00:37:48,200 --> 00:37:50,800
Have Seong Min go to the first floor.

666
00:37:52,300 --> 00:37:55,300
[Chat with Wu Yeol - Second floor living room]

667
00:37:55,310 --> 00:37:58,800
Wu Yeol. The second-floor living room.

668
00:37:58,800 --> 00:38:02,100
- The tea room is here, right?
- Yes, right.

669
00:38:02,130 --> 00:38:04,430
For Seo Won.

670
00:38:04,430 --> 00:38:06,570
Tea room for Seo Won.

671
00:38:06,570 --> 00:38:08,680
[The women are visiting the men]

672
00:38:18,560 --> 00:38:20,340
Gyu Ri chose him first.

673
00:38:20,340 --> 00:38:22,650
- Hello.
- Hello.

674
00:38:23,960 --> 00:38:26,460
- Should I light the candle?
- Yes.

675
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:32,510
[Rule: Chat until the candlelight goes out]

676
00:38:43,150 --> 00:38:44,350
So cute.

677
00:38:44,350 --> 00:38:45,380
[Sipping]

678
00:38:53,290 --> 00:38:55,630
When Seo Won came in,

679
00:38:55,630 --> 00:39:00,680
I thought he was the closest to my type.

680
00:39:00,680 --> 00:39:05,480
I guess I didn't want to show it
since he was so my type.

681
00:39:05,480 --> 00:39:10,030
Since I decided not to show it,

682
00:39:10,030 --> 00:39:13,800
rather than being friendly and smiling,

683
00:39:13,800 --> 00:39:15,200
I suppressed myself.

684
00:39:15,200 --> 00:39:17,230
That's why her eyes moved around.

685
00:39:17,230 --> 00:39:19,920
Yes. I could tell.

686
00:39:19,920 --> 00:39:22,350
As I thought initially,

687
00:39:22,350 --> 00:39:25,400
I thought he was handsome.

688
00:39:25,400 --> 00:39:27,290
He's handsome.

689
00:39:27,300 --> 00:39:30,640
- Gyu Ri is being straightforward.
- Yes. She's honest.

690
00:39:30,640 --> 00:39:33,510
[First chat with her ideal type]

691
00:39:39,470 --> 00:39:42,150
She doesn't know what to do.

692
00:39:42,150 --> 00:39:44,040
What kind of food do you like?

693
00:39:44,040 --> 00:39:46,170
- Food?
- Yes.

694
00:39:47,500 --> 00:39:50,170
I think I eat everything.

695
00:39:50,170 --> 00:39:52,870
I like noodles a lot.

696
00:39:52,870 --> 00:39:58,040
Meat. Meat and fish, those two.

697
00:39:58,040 --> 00:40:00,970
Do you like grilled fish? Hairtail and stuff?

698
00:40:00,970 --> 00:40:04,280
I love it. I love grilled toothfish, too.

699
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:07,210
Sushi and sashimi.

700
00:40:07,210 --> 00:40:08,660
What about you?

701
00:40:08,660 --> 00:40:11,520
I'm the same.

702
00:40:11,520 --> 00:40:13,810
Noodles, sushi, and sashimi.

703
00:40:13,810 --> 00:40:16,210
Yes. I love them.

704
00:40:17,650 --> 00:40:19,070
[Hmm]

705
00:40:19,070 --> 00:40:22,280
[Brief reaction]

706
00:40:28,250 --> 00:40:30,950
What time do you go to work tomorrow?

707
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:34,600
I think I need to leave by 9.

708
00:40:34,600 --> 00:40:38,460
- 9 o'clock?
- I need to leave by 9, at least.

709
00:40:40,060 --> 00:40:42,290
You'll have to go to bed early.

710
00:40:43,430 --> 00:40:44,860
Yes.

711
00:40:45,860 --> 00:40:47,100
Their conversation is too...

712
00:40:47,100 --> 00:40:49,660
- It's choppy, isn't it?
- It's too dry.

713
00:40:49,660 --> 00:40:51,530
Oh, no.

714
00:40:53,750 --> 00:40:58,290
I could just tell that he wasn't interested.

715
00:40:58,290 --> 00:40:59,960
Gyu Ri sensed it.

716
00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:05,200
It was hard for me to talk.

717
00:41:05,200 --> 00:41:06,280
[Running out of time]

718
00:41:06,280 --> 00:41:11,590
We were silent for almost half of the time.

719
00:41:13,320 --> 00:41:18,350
Have you chatted with someone privately like this?

720
00:41:19,330 --> 00:41:21,030
Blind dates, maybe?

721
00:41:21,030 --> 00:41:23,320
Blind dates?

722
00:41:23,320 --> 00:41:26,340
I've never been on one.

723
00:41:26,340 --> 00:41:28,030
- Really?
- Yes.

724
00:41:28,030 --> 00:41:32,660
I thought, "Is he lying?" I was suspicious.

725
00:41:32,660 --> 00:41:33,760
[The light is going off]

726
00:41:33,760 --> 00:41:35,520
It's off now.

727
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:41,000
Did the others light theirs later?

728
00:41:41,060 --> 00:41:44,870
Probably not. I think we were last.

729
00:41:44,870 --> 00:41:47,240
We agreed to go around like this.

730
00:41:47,240 --> 00:41:50,440
Right. While I'm here.

731
00:41:51,310 --> 00:41:53,160
It was fun.

732
00:41:56,900 --> 00:41:58,240
Crazy.

733
00:41:58,240 --> 00:41:59,570
What will she do?

734
00:41:59,570 --> 00:42:01,470
[The first 1:1 didn't go as expected]

735
00:42:07,040 --> 00:42:09,350
Okay. Thank you.

736
00:42:09,350 --> 00:42:12,470
When the flame went off, he was like, "Goodbye."

737
00:42:12,470 --> 00:42:13,790
Goodbye.

738
00:42:13,790 --> 00:42:18,190
I could tell people are giggling outside.

739
00:42:18,190 --> 00:42:21,430
But he said, "Goodbye." I had to go.

740
00:42:21,430 --> 00:42:23,210
Take care.

741
00:42:23,210 --> 00:42:25,600
I thought, "This is his style.

742
00:42:25,600 --> 00:42:28,510
He's not interested at all."

743
00:42:30,460 --> 00:42:33,610
I've never seen a beginning
like this on Heart Signal.

744
00:42:33,610 --> 00:42:34,960
He was so cold.

745
00:42:34,960 --> 00:42:36,890
Gyu Ri seemed a bit offended.

746
00:42:36,890 --> 00:42:39,400
- She's a bit angry.
- She's so sensitive.

747
00:42:39,400 --> 00:42:43,100
- I'd feel that way, too.
- She caught on to everything.

748
00:42:43,100 --> 00:42:44,480
I know.

749
00:42:44,480 --> 00:42:47,550
Her feelings were hurt on the first day.

750
00:42:48,930 --> 00:42:53,580
I don't like someone who doesn't like me.

751
00:42:53,580 --> 00:42:56,120
Of course, she doesn't.

752
00:42:57,770 --> 00:43:01,080
He'd better not fall for her later.

753
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:06,230
But it could be dangerous
if he's a tiny bit nice to her.

754
00:43:06,230 --> 00:43:09,630
She'd think, "I was wrong."

755
00:43:09,630 --> 00:43:11,880
I know.

756
00:43:11,880 --> 00:43:14,650
[Park Wu Yeol and Jeong Gyu Ri]

757
00:43:15,500 --> 00:43:20,800
- Wu Yeol was slightly interested in her.
- Did your first chat go well?

758
00:43:20,860 --> 00:43:23,790
Yes. You should ask like that.

759
00:43:23,790 --> 00:43:28,620
We could barely have a conversation.

760
00:43:28,620 --> 00:43:29,930
Why?

761
00:43:29,930 --> 00:43:31,680
I'm not sure.

762
00:43:32,540 --> 00:43:34,000
Because he's shy?

763
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:37,260
I'm not sure. He didn't seem shy.

764
00:43:37,260 --> 00:43:38,880
I think...

765
00:43:39,830 --> 00:43:41,450
I think...

766
00:43:42,520 --> 00:43:44,730
- He wasn't sure?
- Yes.

767
00:43:47,700 --> 00:43:50,160
He's clenching his fist.

768
00:43:50,160 --> 00:43:51,440
You bastard.

769
00:43:51,440 --> 00:43:54,380
How dare you treat Gyu Ri like that?

770
00:43:54,380 --> 00:43:55,760
[Glancing]

771
00:43:58,900 --> 00:44:00,890
[Smiling]

772
00:44:03,060 --> 00:44:04,790
Why are you checking my reaction?

773
00:44:04,800 --> 00:44:07,300
- She's laughing.
- She's finally laughing.

774
00:44:07,300 --> 00:44:10,130
She can catch a breath here.

775
00:44:10,130 --> 00:44:12,080
Do you go to work tomorrow?

776
00:44:12,080 --> 00:44:13,900
Yes. Do you?

777
00:44:13,900 --> 00:44:15,450
Yes.

778
00:44:15,450 --> 00:44:17,690
- Do you leave in the morning?
- Yes.

779
00:44:17,690 --> 00:44:22,130
I'll probably leave by 9.

780
00:44:22,130 --> 00:44:24,040
- I think I will, too.
- Really?

781
00:44:24,100 --> 00:44:27,900
- Where are you going to?
- I'm going to Yeonnam-dong.

782
00:44:27,920 --> 00:44:29,440
What about you?

783
00:44:29,440 --> 00:44:32,310
I'm near Konkuk University.

784
00:44:32,310 --> 00:44:35,620
It's totally the opposite direction.

785
00:44:35,620 --> 00:44:38,460
What are you taking? Subway?

786
00:44:38,460 --> 00:44:42,040
Wow. I haven't thought about that. Wow.

787
00:44:45,490 --> 00:44:46,590
I guess I should.

788
00:44:46,590 --> 00:44:49,000
Should I drop you off on the way?

789
00:44:49,000 --> 00:44:51,000
- Yes. Sounds good.
- If we leave together.

790
00:44:51,000 --> 00:44:54,280
- Thank you.
- I'll drop you off at the station.

791
00:44:54,280 --> 00:44:57,090
- He said it first.
- He totally likes her.

792
00:44:57,090 --> 00:44:59,170
That was a good timing.

793
00:45:00,080 --> 00:45:02,350
So, about the order...

794
00:45:03,350 --> 00:45:05,750
Did you win and choose or...

795
00:45:05,750 --> 00:45:07,690
I won first place.

796
00:45:07,690 --> 00:45:09,310
- Really?
- Yes.

797
00:45:09,310 --> 00:45:13,560
So, this is the order I chose.

798
00:45:16,320 --> 00:45:20,940
When I saw Gyu Ri...

799
00:45:20,940 --> 00:45:25,930
I think I felt attracted to her.

800
00:45:25,930 --> 00:45:27,890
It showed.

801
00:45:29,280 --> 00:45:31,310
Her eyes are big.

802
00:45:32,450 --> 00:45:35,720
She's a bit cat-like, too.

803
00:45:35,720 --> 00:45:38,080
Yeol or Ryeol?

804
00:45:38,080 --> 00:45:41,710
She has a pretty smile, too.

805
00:45:41,710 --> 00:45:43,050
Your name...

806
00:45:43,050 --> 00:45:46,640
I think I glanced at her without realizing it.

807
00:45:46,640 --> 00:45:48,450
[They ran out of time quickly]

808
00:45:48,450 --> 00:45:50,130
The flame died.

809
00:45:51,110 --> 00:45:53,260
So sad.

810
00:45:57,090 --> 00:45:58,960
Gyu Ri seems interested, right?

811
00:45:58,960 --> 00:46:01,510
She got scratched earlier.

812
00:46:01,510 --> 00:46:02,560
Right.

813
00:46:02,560 --> 00:46:06,720
She met him afterward, but he was so kind.

814
00:46:06,720 --> 00:46:07,900
So warm.

815
