1081
00:59:03,770 --> 00:59:06,280
You did, right?

1082
00:59:06,280 --> 00:59:08,300
Me, too. Right?

1083
00:59:08,300 --> 00:59:10,760
ENTJs are...

1084
00:59:10,760 --> 00:59:12,860
You've been outed now.

1085
00:59:12,860 --> 00:59:15,030
Did you increase the playback speed?

1086
00:59:15,030 --> 00:59:18,560
I watch at about 2.3 or 2.4.

1087
00:59:18,560 --> 00:59:22,450
- Heart Signal on YouTube...
- This is no good.

1088
00:59:22,450 --> 00:59:25,410
I made plans like an ENTJ would.

1089
00:59:25,410 --> 00:59:27,820
But I failed immediately.

1090
00:59:27,820 --> 00:59:29,920
I think I know how it ended.

1091
00:59:30,840 --> 00:59:32,130
They will become friends.

1092
00:59:32,130 --> 00:59:33,710
They won't have any chemistry.

1093
00:59:33,710 --> 00:59:36,230
It's over now. It's over.

1094
00:59:36,230 --> 00:59:39,450
- No.
- They're just friends.

1095
00:59:39,450 --> 00:59:41,700
[Park Wu Yeol and Kang Yu Gyeong]

1096
00:59:47,850 --> 00:59:48,650
[Turning]

1097
00:59:48,650 --> 00:59:51,370
It was Wu Yeol.

1098
00:59:54,730 --> 00:59:57,400
I thought he was really handsome.

1099
00:59:57,400 --> 00:59:59,940
She likes that type.

1100
00:59:59,940 --> 01:00:02,660
He's a tofu type.

1101
01:00:02,660 --> 01:00:08,450
He has a very clean look.

1102
01:00:08,450 --> 01:00:14,420
Look-wise, he's exactly my type.

1103
01:00:14,420 --> 01:00:17,020
Do you know this area well?

1104
01:00:17,020 --> 01:00:20,250
No. I don't come here often.

1105
01:00:20,250 --> 01:00:22,290
- Not too well.
- They're different.

1106
01:00:22,290 --> 01:00:23,670
Do you?

1107
01:00:23,670 --> 01:00:25,150
I know nothing.

1108
01:00:25,150 --> 01:00:27,940
Really? Which area do you know well?

1109
01:00:30,350 --> 01:00:32,070
It's a secret.

1110
01:00:33,050 --> 01:00:34,980
Her voice changed.

1111
01:00:34,980 --> 01:00:36,560
Got it.

1112
01:00:37,330 --> 01:00:40,240
Do you leave work in the evening?

1113
01:00:40,240 --> 01:00:41,790
I think I'll be back early.

1114
01:00:41,790 --> 01:00:43,320
I see.

1115
01:00:46,050 --> 01:00:48,050
You're so cautious.

1116
01:00:48,050 --> 01:00:51,150
Do you not want to tell me?

1117
01:00:51,150 --> 01:00:53,290
It's not that. I don't want
to say the wrong thing.

1118
01:00:53,290 --> 01:00:56,170
Isn't this a massage chair?

1119
01:00:57,230 --> 01:00:59,730
Do you struggle to focus on one thing?

1120
01:00:59,730 --> 01:01:02,780
No, no. I'm a bit out of it right now.

1121
01:01:02,800 --> 01:01:05,280
- Because she likes him.
- Right.

1122
01:01:05,280 --> 01:01:06,890
Are you able to focus?

1123
01:01:06,890 --> 01:01:09,120
I'm doing fine.

1124
01:01:11,720 --> 01:01:13,780
You seem calm.

1125
01:01:13,780 --> 01:01:16,320
I pretend to be calm.

1126
01:01:17,110 --> 01:01:20,550
Did you just ask if I had ADHD?

1127
01:01:20,550 --> 01:01:23,470
When did I... When did I say that?

1128
01:01:23,470 --> 01:01:26,070
I don't see the difference.

1129
01:01:26,070 --> 01:01:28,950
It did cross my mind.

1130
01:01:28,950 --> 01:01:31,140
I'm not.

1131
01:01:31,140 --> 01:01:32,360
Okay.

1132
01:01:32,360 --> 01:01:35,070
It's because I'm embarrassed.

1133
01:01:35,070 --> 01:01:36,810
I can see that.

1134
01:01:42,120 --> 01:01:44,210
It's funny.

1135
01:01:45,670 --> 01:01:48,360
No, what is...

1136
01:01:50,980 --> 01:01:53,570
I'm suspecting a messy dynamic here.

1137
01:01:53,570 --> 01:01:55,450
I think you're right.

1138
01:01:56,430 --> 01:02:00,970
Your personality seems unexpected...

1139
01:02:02,560 --> 01:02:04,830
in a fun way.

1140
01:02:04,830 --> 01:02:07,770
Who? Really?

1141
01:02:10,590 --> 01:02:14,350
I won't say it. Later, later.

1142
01:02:14,350 --> 01:02:15,750
- Later.
- I'll tell you later.

1143
01:02:15,750 --> 01:02:17,460
Once we get to know each other more.

1144
01:02:17,500 --> 01:02:21,400
I think I should stop here today.

1145
01:02:21,400 --> 01:02:22,490
[Glancing]

1146
01:02:22,490 --> 01:02:24,260
Are you afraid you'll hurt me?

1147
01:02:24,260 --> 01:02:26,560
Do you get hurt?

1148
01:02:26,560 --> 01:02:29,710
I do. I'm an F.

1149
01:02:33,320 --> 01:02:35,170
You seem so fun.

1150
01:02:36,670 --> 01:02:39,060
You seem...

1151
01:02:40,880 --> 01:02:43,010
quirkier than you look.

1152
01:02:45,610 --> 01:02:47,050
What?

1153
01:02:48,580 --> 01:02:51,600
I wanted to hide that.

1154
01:02:51,600 --> 01:02:55,120
I know. You can't hide it.

1155
01:02:56,340 --> 01:02:57,970
That's not all there is.

1156
01:02:57,970 --> 01:02:59,810
They have a bit of a spark, too.

1157
01:02:59,810 --> 01:03:01,740
But I find it fun.

1158
01:03:01,740 --> 01:03:02,940
Really?

1159
01:03:02,940 --> 01:03:04,780
Why are you making that face...

1160
01:03:04,780 --> 01:03:08,460
Why do I keep doing that? I can't.

1161
01:03:08,460 --> 01:03:10,340
I find it fun.

1162
01:03:15,940 --> 01:03:18,110
You seem different.

1163
01:03:19,520 --> 01:03:21,370
Because it's unexpected?

1164
01:03:21,370 --> 01:03:22,710
Yes.

1165
01:03:22,710 --> 01:03:26,530
You seem more...

1166
01:03:30,260 --> 01:03:32,100
[Hesitant]

1167
01:03:34,550 --> 01:03:36,260
positive.

1168
01:03:38,290 --> 01:03:42,880
Since things have been chaotic,

1169
01:03:42,880 --> 01:03:45,620
I didn't get to look closely.

1170
01:03:45,620 --> 01:03:47,720
But I think you're...

1171
01:03:54,100 --> 01:03:57,800
- more charming than expected.
- Oh, really?

1172
01:03:58,930 --> 01:04:01,350
You... You're fun.

1173
01:04:01,350 --> 01:04:02,960
It's a compliment.

1174
01:04:02,960 --> 01:04:04,560
Thank you.

1175
01:04:06,550 --> 01:04:10,470
[Park Wu Yeol said something unexpected]

1176
01:04:11,080 --> 01:04:13,670
[How did Yu Gyeong feel about it?]

1177
01:04:13,700 --> 01:04:15,900
- Wu Yeol is so cool.
- I know.

1178
01:04:15,900 --> 01:04:19,400
He's very calm with a woman who shows interest.

1179
01:04:19,420 --> 01:04:21,960
He must be experienced.

1180
01:04:21,960 --> 01:04:24,420
I find your personality unexpected, too.

1181
01:04:24,420 --> 01:04:27,130
Really? Like, reserved?

1182
01:04:27,130 --> 01:04:32,800
Yes. I expected you to be more reserved.

1183
01:04:32,800 --> 01:04:35,250
[Flustered]

1184
01:04:35,250 --> 01:04:37,490
I'm not saying you aren't at all.

1185
01:04:37,490 --> 01:04:40,580
But you're a bit different than I expected.

1186
01:04:40,580 --> 01:04:43,290
Is that a good thing?

1187
01:04:43,290 --> 01:04:45,130
It was a compliment.

1188
01:04:47,250 --> 01:04:51,690
Something about it bothered me.

1189
01:04:51,690 --> 01:04:54,070
He seems seasoned.

1190
01:04:54,070 --> 01:04:57,660
He seems to know women well.

1191
01:04:57,660 --> 01:04:59,730
You tease people easily, huh?

1192
01:04:59,730 --> 01:05:02,400
Could you say I read people well?

1193
01:05:02,400 --> 01:05:04,890
That I'm good at reading people?

1194
01:05:04,890 --> 01:05:09,680
You read people and attack them.

1195
01:05:11,090 --> 01:05:12,280
Kind of.

1196
01:05:12,280 --> 01:05:13,930
Is he cunning?

1197
01:05:13,930 --> 01:05:17,310
I know. She can think that.

1198
01:05:17,310 --> 01:05:18,690
Time went by so fast.

1199
01:05:18,690 --> 01:05:22,100
I know. Yes. It seems so.

1200
01:05:23,050 --> 01:05:25,920
I like men who aren't smooth.

1201
01:05:25,920 --> 01:05:28,360
Because I'm not.

1202
01:05:28,360 --> 01:05:33,230
He seemed too seasoned.

1203
01:05:33,230 --> 01:05:37,200
I think he'll play me easily.

1204
01:05:37,200 --> 01:05:44,000
I trust people so easily and believe what I see.

1205
01:05:45,100 --> 01:05:49,630
I've been hurt by being that way.

1206
01:05:50,630 --> 01:05:54,230
I thought I should be careful.

1207
01:05:54,230 --> 01:05:56,630
I built up a bit of a wall.

1208
01:05:56,630 --> 01:05:58,540
Why build a wall?

1209
01:05:58,540 --> 01:06:00,720
Yu Gyeong feels that way

1210
01:06:00,720 --> 01:06:03,310
because he hasn't fallen for her yet.

1211
01:06:03,310 --> 01:06:05,710
That's true. That's true.

1212
01:06:05,710 --> 01:06:09,890
He thinks of her as someone
to get along with, but she...

1213
01:06:09,900 --> 01:06:12,400
- Don't jump to conclusion yet.
- No, just for now.

1214
01:06:12,400 --> 01:06:15,300
- But they...
- Wu Yeol isn't smitten yet.

1215
01:06:15,300 --> 01:06:17,690
- Yu Gyeong is smitten.
- She is.

1216
01:06:17,690 --> 01:06:19,810
I know. I know.

1217
01:06:19,810 --> 01:06:22,250
It disadvantages you in the relationship.

1218
01:06:22,300 --> 01:06:26,000
If she falls so hard for him,
she knows she'll lose.

1219
01:06:26,030 --> 01:06:28,320
So, she's putting a shackle on herself.

1220
01:06:28,320 --> 01:06:30,470
Yu Gyeong is interesting. I like her personality.

1221
01:06:30,470 --> 01:06:34,290
I thought she'd be more experienced and older,

1222
01:06:34,290 --> 01:06:38,340
but she gets clumsy in front of her crush.

1223
01:06:38,340 --> 01:06:41,750
She just thought he was handsome,

1224
01:06:41,750 --> 01:06:44,510
but he's also smooth. And she's smitten.

1225
01:06:44,510 --> 01:06:47,060
She's afraid that she's smitten.

1226
01:06:47,060 --> 01:06:50,070
She keeps telling herself that she can't be.

1227
01:06:50,070 --> 01:06:51,830
She thinks that because she is.

1228
01:06:51,830 --> 01:06:53,350
She's smitten. She's smitten.

1229
01:06:53,350 --> 01:06:56,860
I love this so much. This is it.

1230
01:06:56,860 --> 01:06:58,520
[Signal House's first evening has come]

1231
01:06:58,520 --> 01:07:01,470
- So pretty.
- It's the evening.

1232
01:07:03,430 --> 01:07:06,720
It's time to eat now.

1233
01:07:06,720 --> 01:07:08,620
Let's designate cooks.

1234
01:07:08,620 --> 01:07:09,960
Okay.

1235
01:07:10,830 --> 01:07:12,280
How should we do it?

1236
01:07:12,280 --> 01:07:14,630
Rock, paper, scissors, and pair up?

1237
01:07:14,630 --> 01:07:17,010
- Sounds good.
- Shall we?

1238
01:07:17,010 --> 01:07:19,710
We'll form three teams.

1239
01:07:19,710 --> 01:07:21,590
Okay, okay.

1240
01:07:21,590 --> 01:07:24,110
Rock, paper, scissors.

1241
01:07:24,110 --> 01:07:26,280
[First round fails]

1242
01:07:26,280 --> 01:07:28,230
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- It worked.

1243
01:07:28,230 --> 01:07:30,620
Gyu Ri and Seong Min.

1244
01:07:30,620 --> 01:07:33,350
The four of us? Rock, paper, scissors.

1245
01:07:33,350 --> 01:07:34,430
We're done.

1246
01:07:34,430 --> 01:07:35,690
[Yu Gyeong and Wu Yeol]

1247
01:07:35,690 --> 01:07:37,800
[Min Ju and Seo Won]

1248
01:07:37,800 --> 01:07:40,300
- Starting today?
- Three days.

1249
01:07:40,300 --> 01:07:42,060
Thursday, Friday, Saturday.

1250
01:07:42,060 --> 01:07:43,600
In what order?

1251
01:07:43,600 --> 01:07:45,070
Do you want to play for us?

1252
01:07:45,070 --> 01:07:46,270
Me?

1253
01:07:46,270 --> 01:07:47,600
- Do you want to?
- I'll do it.

1254
01:07:47,600 --> 01:07:49,480
They're in a good mood.

1255
01:07:49,500 --> 01:07:52,200
- Are you good at rock, paper, scissors?
- I'm good.

1256
01:07:52,210 --> 01:07:53,530
Play for us, then.

1257
01:07:53,530 --> 01:07:54,870
Shall we?

1258
01:07:54,870 --> 01:07:56,580
Rock, paper, scissors.

1259
01:07:56,580 --> 01:07:58,270
Wow. You're good.

1260
01:07:58,270 --> 01:08:00,290
Rock, paper, scissors. Rock, paper, scissors.

1261
01:08:00,290 --> 01:08:01,940
[Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong: 1st place /
Seo Won and Min Ju: 2nd place]

1262
01:08:01,940 --> 01:08:03,030
[Bragging]

1263
01:08:03,030 --> 01:08:04,830
She seems like a goofball.

1264
01:08:04,830 --> 01:08:05,670
[Thumb up]

1265
01:08:05,670 --> 01:08:06,700
Should we cook tonight?

1266
01:08:06,700 --> 01:08:08,380
- Tonight?
- No? You don't want to?

1267
01:08:08,380 --> 01:08:09,420
Sounds good.

1268
01:08:09,420 --> 01:08:11,700
Tonight? Sounds good.

1269
01:08:11,700 --> 01:08:13,640
Sounds good.

1270
01:08:13,640 --> 01:08:17,230
The first night. It's better to get it over with.

1271
01:08:17,230 --> 01:08:18,500
Right.

1272
01:08:18,500 --> 01:08:20,130
Should we cook tonight?

1273
01:08:20,130 --> 01:08:21,070
He's not happy.

1274
01:08:21,070 --> 01:08:23,760
- Sounds good.
- We'll go first.

1275
01:08:23,760 --> 01:08:25,310
Seo Won is so transparent.

1276
01:08:25,310 --> 01:08:27,910
[Lights are turning on one by one in Itaewon]

1277
01:08:29,040 --> 01:08:31,150
[Checking the refrigerator]

1278
01:08:34,950 --> 01:08:36,620
[Surprised]

1279
01:08:36,620 --> 01:08:38,920
What? What?

1280
01:08:40,510 --> 01:08:42,170
I'm getting butterflies.

1281
01:08:42,200 --> 01:08:46,200
- She built a wall, and he's there.
- What's with him?

1282
01:08:46,200 --> 01:08:48,800
He's doing it more now.

1283
01:08:48,800 --> 01:08:51,100
[Surprised]

1284
01:08:54,900 --> 01:08:57,400
What are we doing? Meat?

1285
01:08:57,460 --> 01:09:00,280
What should go with meat?

1286
01:09:00,300 --> 01:09:03,070
How do you normally eat?

1287
01:09:03,070 --> 01:09:05,420
What do you usually eat at home?

1288
01:09:05,420 --> 01:09:08,270
He's standing there like a fridge model?

1289
01:09:08,270 --> 01:09:11,310
Leaning on the fridge is cool.

1290
01:09:11,310 --> 01:09:13,850
I know. I should learn from him.

1291
01:09:13,850 --> 01:09:16,340
What do you usually eat at home?

1292
01:09:16,340 --> 01:09:18,170
What do you normally eat?

1293
01:09:18,170 --> 01:09:21,840
I tend to eat...

1294
01:09:21,840 --> 01:09:26,350
irregularly and unhealthily.
I don't know what to say.

1295
01:09:26,350 --> 01:09:27,970
What do you usually eat?

1296
01:09:27,970 --> 01:09:30,300
I eat frozen fried rice.

1297
01:09:30,300 --> 01:09:32,600
Pre-made food?

1298
01:09:32,600 --> 01:09:35,440
I'm getting a clear sense now.

1299
01:09:37,220 --> 01:09:39,700
Neither of them can cook.

1300
01:09:40,650 --> 01:09:42,850
Let's sear meat.

1301
01:09:42,850 --> 01:09:44,460
I'll do it.

1302
01:09:44,460 --> 01:09:46,770
There's pasta and stuff over there.

1303
01:09:46,770 --> 01:09:49,410
Where was it?

1304
01:09:49,500 --> 01:09:52,600
- Are you good at making pasta?
- No.

1305
01:09:52,640 --> 01:09:54,820
[Laughing out of worry]

1306
01:09:54,820 --> 01:09:56,350
We shouldn't have volunteered tonight.

1307
01:09:56,350 --> 01:09:58,350
I'll prep the ingredients.

1308
01:09:58,350 --> 01:10:00,030
Okay. Do whatever you prefer.

1309
01:10:00,030 --> 01:10:01,610
Please take care of cooking.

1310
01:10:01,610 --> 01:10:03,310
[Turning around]

1311
01:10:03,310 --> 01:10:04,680
Butter?

1312
01:10:04,680 --> 01:10:07,180
Add butter to the meat?

1313
01:10:07,180 --> 01:10:08,920
[Handing over]

1314
01:10:09,350 --> 01:10:10,670
You're good at handing stuff over.

1315
01:10:10,670 --> 01:10:12,720
No, no. For the meat...

1316
01:10:12,720 --> 01:10:14,730
I'll make the pasta.

1317
01:10:14,730 --> 01:10:16,450
[Looking up recipes]

1318
01:10:16,450 --> 01:10:18,880
I can ask AI, right?

1319
01:10:18,880 --> 01:10:20,230
Ask it.

1320
01:10:20,230 --> 01:10:22,270
I'll photograph the meat and...

1321
01:10:22,270 --> 01:10:25,140
How should we grill these?

1322
01:10:25,140 --> 01:10:27,610
How is it so quiet?

1323
01:10:27,610 --> 01:10:29,460
It's working, right?

1324
01:10:29,460 --> 01:10:31,690
I put it in the wrong spot.

1325
01:10:32,870 --> 01:10:34,860
Yu Gyeong can't stop laughing.

1326
01:10:34,860 --> 01:10:37,100
That's what I thought.

1327
01:10:37,100 --> 01:10:38,540
She's starting to talk casually.

1328
01:10:38,540 --> 01:10:39,910
Black pepper.

1329
01:10:39,910 --> 01:10:44,080
Pepper and herbs? Perfect.

1330
01:10:44,080 --> 01:10:45,650
I can do this, right?

1331
01:10:45,650 --> 01:10:47,970
Gosh. Fighting.

1332
01:10:47,970 --> 01:10:49,440
In here...

1333
01:10:49,440 --> 01:10:51,230
- Add oil...
- Olive oil?

1334
01:10:51,230 --> 01:10:53,310
And salt.

1335
01:10:53,310 --> 01:10:55,180
I'll wipe this off later.

1336
01:10:55,180 --> 01:10:57,130
It told me to.

1337
01:10:57,200 --> 01:11:00,100
- AI did?
- Yes.

1338
01:11:00,100 --> 01:11:04,800
- Nice vibe.
- Wu Yeol puts you at ease.

1339
01:11:04,800 --> 01:11:08,050
Working together in the kitchen...

1340
01:11:08,050 --> 01:11:12,930
feels like playing pretend, you know.

1341
01:11:12,930 --> 01:11:14,290
Fighting.

1342
01:11:14,290 --> 01:11:15,860
[Cutting awkwardly]

1343
01:11:15,860 --> 01:11:17,610
I think...

1344
01:11:19,250 --> 01:11:21,440
it's coming together.

1345
01:11:21,440 --> 01:11:23,820
What is? Us?

1346
01:11:23,820 --> 01:11:25,430
Of course.

1347
01:11:26,900 --> 01:11:28,460
I have faith.

1348
01:11:30,710 --> 01:11:33,200
How much garlic should I use?

1349
01:11:33,200 --> 01:11:34,600
[Leaning over]

1350
01:11:38,270 --> 01:11:41,320
Salt should taste like seawater.

1351
01:11:42,450 --> 01:11:46,960
It feels like we've known each other for days.

1352
01:11:46,960 --> 01:11:49,390
Really? Too familiar?

1353
01:11:50,270 --> 01:11:51,700
I should keep a distance.

1354
01:11:51,700 --> 01:11:53,830
She keeps saying that.

1355
01:11:55,840 --> 01:11:57,230
This.

1356
01:11:58,080 --> 01:11:59,680
Seawater.

1357
01:12:06,100 --> 01:12:08,500
- I'm sweating bullets.
- Fighting.

1358
01:12:08,500 --> 01:12:11,000
You were doing stuff.

1359
01:12:11,030 --> 01:12:12,170
[The male tenants are in the kitchen]

1360
01:12:12,170 --> 01:12:14,100
Huh? They're all here.

1361
01:12:15,010 --> 01:12:17,560
Her face says, "Why are you here?"

1362
01:12:17,560 --> 01:12:20,040
She's like, "What's with you guys?"

1363
01:12:20,100 --> 01:12:23,300
- What's with you guys?
- Why are you here?

1364
01:12:24,990 --> 01:12:28,400
Shouldn't we lend you a hand?

1365
01:12:28,400 --> 01:12:30,500
- He won't say anything.
- Let us help you.

1366
01:12:30,530 --> 01:12:32,040
Do you know how to make pasta?

1367
01:12:32,040 --> 01:12:33,130
[Glancing]

1368
01:12:33,130 --> 01:12:34,220
No.

1369
01:12:34,220 --> 01:12:36,310
You just add everything, right?

1370
01:12:36,310 --> 01:12:37,650
Come on now.

1371
01:12:37,650 --> 01:12:39,250
They came and ruined things.

1372
01:12:39,250 --> 01:12:40,920
- Is this soap?
- I think so.

1373
01:12:40,920 --> 01:12:43,450
I washed my hands with that earlier.

1374
01:12:46,310 --> 01:12:47,800
[Washing]

1375
01:12:47,800 --> 01:12:51,140
Could you teach me? I need to learn.

1376
01:12:51,140 --> 01:12:53,160
Who's teaching whom?

1377
01:12:53,160 --> 01:12:55,750
Yu Gyeong can't hide her feelings.

1378
01:12:55,750 --> 01:12:57,150
She's honest.

1379
01:12:57,150 --> 01:12:58,520
[Staring]

1380
01:12:58,520 --> 01:13:00,240
With this...

1381
01:13:00,240 --> 01:13:03,730
[Same room, different emotions]

1382
01:13:05,520 --> 01:13:07,790
[Glancing]

1383
01:13:08,810 --> 01:13:10,500
[Rubbing]

1384
01:13:11,810 --> 01:13:13,420
How long is he washing his hands?

1385
01:13:13,420 --> 01:13:14,820
[Washing hands skillfully]

1386
01:13:17,040 --> 01:13:19,180
He's a doctor. That was obvious.

1387
01:13:19,180 --> 01:13:21,630
You can tell.

1388
01:13:21,630 --> 01:13:24,310
Did he out himself on purpose?

1389
01:13:24,310 --> 01:13:27,500
It's not necessary now. He's cooking.

1390
01:13:27,500 --> 01:13:30,100
Maybe he's just germophobic.

1391
01:13:30,100 --> 01:13:31,940
[What's this?]

1392
01:13:33,340 --> 01:13:35,790
- I'm starting to get it.
- Okay.

1393
01:13:35,790 --> 01:13:38,090
[Staring]

1394
01:13:38,090 --> 01:13:39,920
We'll be okay, right?

1395
01:13:39,920 --> 01:13:42,410
I'm good at eating bad food.

1396
01:13:42,410 --> 01:13:43,760
- Yu Gyeong.
- Yes?

1397
01:13:43,760 --> 01:13:45,750
Can I help you with anything?

1398
01:13:45,750 --> 01:13:47,210
[Seo Won is approaching her]

1399
01:13:47,210 --> 01:13:49,510
Watch your fingers.

1400
01:13:49,510 --> 01:13:52,260
Curl your fingers like this.

1401
01:13:52,260 --> 01:13:54,320
He can tell everyone likes her.

1402
01:13:54,320 --> 01:13:56,870
He's sensing that.

1403
01:13:56,870 --> 01:13:58,860
This is our first time cooking.

1404
01:13:58,860 --> 01:14:01,890
Let us know if you need anything.

1405
01:14:01,900 --> 01:14:04,670
- Could you slice onion?
- I'll slice it.

1406
01:14:04,670 --> 01:14:06,720
- Did you wash your hands?
- I've been wanting to do it.

1407
01:14:06,720 --> 01:14:08,690
Be careful.

1408
01:14:08,690 --> 01:14:11,010
- Do it like this, right?
- Is this your first time?

1409
01:14:11,010 --> 01:14:13,210
- Yes.
- Turn this around, then.

1410
01:14:13,210 --> 01:14:14,550
Turn it around like this...

1411
01:14:14,550 --> 01:14:16,680
Seo Won was so quiet earlier.

1412
01:14:16,680 --> 01:14:17,820
I know.

1413
01:14:17,820 --> 01:14:19,710
What are the other two doing?

1414
01:14:19,710 --> 01:14:23,470
They need to see the three men in the kitchen.

1415
01:14:23,470 --> 01:14:25,190
It's ridiculous right now.

1416
01:14:25,190 --> 01:14:27,890
That's such a sore sight.

1417
01:14:27,890 --> 01:14:28,820
[Checking her face]

1418
01:14:31,490 --> 01:14:32,810
Why don't we start...

1419
01:14:32,810 --> 01:14:34,750
I really need moisturizer.

1420
01:14:34,750 --> 01:14:35,940
I know.

1421
01:14:35,940 --> 01:14:37,670
It's so dry in here.

1422
01:14:37,670 --> 01:14:39,800
Hurry up. Let's go.

1423
01:14:39,800 --> 01:14:40,960
They need to go quickly.

1424
01:14:40,960 --> 01:14:42,810
Hurry up.

1425
01:14:42,810 --> 01:14:44,330
It's so quiet.

1426
01:14:44,330 --> 01:14:46,180
I'm jealous of the men's room.

1427
01:14:46,180 --> 01:14:48,240
Should we switch later?

1428
01:14:49,260 --> 01:14:51,090
Huh? I smell something.

1429
01:14:51,090 --> 01:14:52,680
[Crowded]

1430
01:14:52,680 --> 01:14:55,280
It's ridiculous right now.

1431
01:14:58,480 --> 01:14:59,350
[Peeping]

1432
01:14:59,350 --> 01:15:02,660
- They're here.
- Come on.

1433
01:15:02,660 --> 01:15:04,670
Are you doing a good job?

1434
01:15:06,360 --> 01:15:09,740
We're trying to help them.

1435
01:15:09,740 --> 01:15:12,140
But we aren't sure where to start.

1436
01:15:12,140 --> 01:15:15,250
It smells tasty.

1437
01:15:15,250 --> 01:15:17,350
They won't look at them.

1438
01:15:19,280 --> 01:15:21,490
[Approaching]

1439
01:15:22,020 --> 01:15:23,920
Approaching Seo Won.

1440
01:15:23,920 --> 01:15:26,940
Did your eyes water? Did your eyes water?

1441
01:15:26,940 --> 01:15:29,550
My eyes? Yes.

1442
01:15:29,550 --> 01:15:31,220
I'm not good at it.

1443
01:15:31,220 --> 01:15:33,040
There was an apron.

1444
01:15:33,040 --> 01:15:35,560
Isn't this an apron?

1445
01:15:35,560 --> 01:15:38,160
[Fidgeting]

1446
01:15:44,690 --> 01:15:47,170
[Lurking]

1447
01:15:49,210 --> 01:15:51,480
Chefs, what should we do?

1448
01:15:51,480 --> 01:15:53,390
There isn't much...

1449
01:15:53,390 --> 01:15:55,100
Nothing to do?

1450
01:15:55,100 --> 01:15:56,550
[They're too busy to answer]

1451
01:15:56,550 --> 01:15:59,770
Everyone's ignoring them.

1452
01:15:59,770 --> 01:16:01,040
[Putting it on]

1453
01:16:01,040 --> 01:16:02,950
He's wearing an apron now.

1454
01:16:04,000 --> 01:16:06,000
Yes. Sear it like that and...

1455
01:16:06,000 --> 01:16:08,990
Wow. Suffocating.

1456
01:16:08,990 --> 01:16:11,450
Seo Won doesn't care about the other women.

1457
01:16:11,450 --> 01:16:12,820
Forget the rules.

1458
01:16:12,820 --> 01:16:16,040
He needs to cook with Yu Gyeong.

1459
01:16:16,040 --> 01:16:17,620
Should I cut the asparagus?

1460
01:16:17,620 --> 01:16:19,980
Just trim the bottom, please.

1461
01:16:19,980 --> 01:16:22,020
He won't leave her alone.

1462
01:16:22,020 --> 01:16:24,730
This is crazy.

1463
01:16:24,730 --> 01:16:27,210
Should I split this in half?

1464
01:16:27,210 --> 01:16:29,020
I shouldn't?

1465
01:16:29,020 --> 01:16:30,530
Okay.

1466
01:16:30,530 --> 01:16:32,160
She's leaving.

1467
01:16:32,160 --> 01:16:34,390
Gyu Ri's personality is showing.

1468
01:16:34,390 --> 01:16:38,470
What do I do? Will I just sleep here and go home?

1469
01:16:38,470 --> 01:16:42,200
I felt that way for the first time
while preparing dinner.

1470
01:16:42,200 --> 01:16:45,960
It's all about physical attraction at this stage.

1471
01:16:45,960 --> 01:16:47,770
Because it's the first day.

1472
01:16:47,770 --> 01:16:52,050
I can't help but look at Seo Won
since he's my partner.

1473
01:16:52,050 --> 01:16:55,240
Right. She should be cooking with Seo Won.

1474
01:16:56,240 --> 01:17:00,060
Why did he put the apron on? I'm curious.

1475
01:17:00,060 --> 01:17:02,560
That's what I'm saying. I know, Min Ju.

1476
01:17:02,560 --> 01:17:05,470
- I know.
- Too much.

1477
01:17:06,400 --> 01:17:11,430
We could've discussed what
to make as cooking partners.

1478
01:17:11,430 --> 01:17:13,100
I want to help.

1479
01:17:13,910 --> 01:17:15,440
Gosh.

1480
01:17:15,440 --> 01:17:16,920
Do you want to cut stuff?

1481
01:17:16,920 --> 01:17:19,190
- Yes.
- Cut stuff?

1482
01:17:19,190 --> 01:17:21,730
This is for the pasta.

1483
01:17:21,730 --> 01:17:25,990
He must've been attracted to Yu Gyeong.

1484
01:17:25,990 --> 01:17:29,710
That must be why he was
wearing an apron. So, I...

1485
01:17:29,710 --> 01:17:32,700
Min Ju knows. Min Ju knows.

1486
01:17:32,700 --> 01:17:36,270
This is where you develop relationships.

1487
01:17:36,270 --> 01:17:40,070
I'm realizing they're exchanging signals.

1488
01:17:40,070 --> 01:17:43,410
You must cook often, Yu Gyeong.

1489
01:17:43,410 --> 01:17:45,230
Well, no.

1490
01:17:45,230 --> 01:17:47,150
I don't really.

1491
01:17:48,080 --> 01:17:50,270
It's not hot.

1492
01:17:52,880 --> 01:17:54,070
[Gulp]

1493
01:17:55,320 --> 01:17:56,480
It's hard, right?

1494
01:17:56,480 --> 01:17:59,450
It will turn into udon.

1495
01:18:00,640 --> 01:18:02,910
Do you want Coke?

1496
01:18:02,910 --> 01:18:04,190
Thank you.

1497
01:18:04,190 --> 01:18:05,420
[Smile]

1498
01:18:05,970 --> 01:18:07,320
What are you doing on Saturday?

1499
01:18:07,320 --> 01:18:10,460
Saturday? Put it here...

1500
01:18:10,460 --> 01:18:12,080
Huh? Why?

1501
01:18:12,080 --> 01:18:14,420
[Seong Min can't hear Gyu Ri]

1502
01:18:14,420 --> 01:18:17,230
She asked, "What are you doing
on Saturday?" but...

1503
01:18:17,230 --> 01:18:18,260
[Speechless]

1504
01:18:18,260 --> 01:18:21,810
Why won't he answer her?

1505
01:18:21,810 --> 01:18:24,470
They're like racing horses.

1506
01:18:24,470 --> 01:18:28,440
[Gyu Ri hasn't gotten her answer]

1507
01:18:28,440 --> 01:18:30,820
My gosh.

1508
01:18:33,600 --> 01:18:36,890
I just need to catch it after a bit.

1509
01:18:36,890 --> 01:18:38,140
[Close, but far]

1510
01:18:38,140 --> 01:18:41,360
They keep standing behind them.

1511
01:18:43,360 --> 01:18:44,190
[Glancing]

1512
01:18:44,920 --> 01:18:47,700
Do you wear the apron often?

1513
01:18:47,700 --> 01:18:50,120
- No.
- Is this your first time?

1514
01:18:51,000 --> 01:18:52,520
Probably.

1515
01:18:53,500 --> 01:18:56,400
- Want to try some meat?
- Sure.

1516
01:19:00,190 --> 01:19:02,320
It was tough then.

1517
01:19:02,320 --> 01:19:05,100
It's tough. It's so tough.

1518
01:19:05,100 --> 01:19:08,300
- Can I help with anything?
- No!

1519
01:19:08,360 --> 01:19:10,670
Don't do anything! Stop it.

1520
01:19:10,670 --> 01:19:12,870
[Never seen anyone like him]

1521
01:19:14,020 --> 01:19:15,620
Can I help with anything?

1522
01:19:15,620 --> 01:19:16,480
[Haha]

1523
01:19:19,030 --> 01:19:21,490
Four helpers are on standby.

1524
01:19:21,490 --> 01:19:24,320
There are too many helpers.

1525
01:19:24,320 --> 01:19:26,880
I wandered aimlessly.

1526
01:19:26,880 --> 01:19:30,560
I didn't know what to do in the kitchen.

1527
01:19:30,560 --> 01:19:33,400
I thought, "Is this how it is?"

1528
01:19:33,400 --> 01:19:34,760
[Leaning]

1529
01:19:36,660 --> 01:19:38,610
I felt scared.

1530
01:19:38,610 --> 01:19:41,390
I thought I could get hurt here.

1531
01:19:41,390 --> 01:19:44,030
Twist it like this?

1532
01:19:45,170 --> 01:19:47,810
I felt a bit hurt.

1533
01:19:49,150 --> 01:19:51,020
Rice.

1534
01:19:51,020 --> 01:19:52,890
Rice.

1535
01:19:52,890 --> 01:19:55,640
I was like, "Let's see."

1536
01:19:55,640 --> 01:19:58,750
Gyu Ri doesn't get hurt and gives up easily.

1537
01:19:58,750 --> 01:20:01,030
Right. She's tough.

1538
01:20:01,960 --> 01:20:04,320
I think we need more.

1539
01:20:04,320 --> 01:20:07,320
- More?
- The sauce, I mean.

1540
01:20:07,320 --> 01:20:08,840
Everyone left.

1541
01:20:08,840 --> 01:20:11,050
I can finally breathe.

1542
01:20:12,050 --> 01:20:14,280
Ah...

1543
01:20:14,280 --> 01:20:18,290
Hold on. Let me taste it.

1544
01:20:18,290 --> 01:20:20,810
Let's see how it tastes now.

1545
01:20:24,530 --> 01:20:27,970
Rice... Should we have it with rice?

1546
01:20:27,970 --> 01:20:29,410
Is it good?

1547
01:20:29,410 --> 01:20:31,170
I don't taste anything.

1548
01:20:31,170 --> 01:20:32,420
Gosh.

1549
01:20:32,420 --> 01:20:36,040
We misjudged the sauce amount.

1550
01:20:36,040 --> 01:20:37,910
- For the steak?
- No.

1551
01:20:37,910 --> 01:20:39,690
They're coming back.

1552
01:20:39,690 --> 01:20:41,300
What's with them?

1553
01:20:41,300 --> 01:20:44,450
They're making me cheer for those two.

1554
01:20:44,450 --> 01:20:45,770
Dopamine is spiking.

1555
01:20:45,770 --> 01:20:47,370
What's wrong with them?

1556
01:20:47,370 --> 01:20:48,650
Did you make too much sauce?

1557
01:20:48,650 --> 01:20:51,000
No, there isn't enough.

1558
01:20:51,000 --> 01:20:53,870
I think we didn't make enough sauce.

1559
01:20:53,870 --> 01:20:56,280
Both of them are terrible cooks.

1560
01:20:56,280 --> 01:21:00,360
It was me. I gave her the wrong directions.

1561
01:21:00,360 --> 01:21:01,750
He's defending her.

1562
01:21:01,750 --> 01:21:03,120
It's sad, isn't it?

1563
01:21:03,120 --> 01:21:05,590
It's 30 servings.

1564
01:21:05,590 --> 01:21:08,430
I don't know much about pasta.

1565
01:21:08,430 --> 01:21:12,180
I think we should get some nearby.

1566
01:21:12,180 --> 01:21:15,720
- Let's turn this off.
- A convenience store?

1567
01:21:17,650 --> 01:21:20,460
Should I stop by a convenience store?

1568
01:21:20,460 --> 01:21:22,630
Gosh.

1569
01:21:23,720 --> 01:21:25,930
I'll go.

1570
01:21:25,930 --> 01:21:27,850
It's okay.

1571
01:21:27,850 --> 01:21:30,610
I think there was one nearby.

1572
01:21:30,610 --> 01:21:31,960
I'll come with you.

1573
01:21:31,960 --> 01:21:34,110
It's a bit far.

1574
01:21:34,110 --> 01:21:35,770
How far?

1575
01:21:35,770 --> 01:21:37,510
Put a coat on.

1576
01:21:37,510 --> 01:21:39,730
It's okay. I'll go like this.

1577
01:21:39,730 --> 01:21:42,470
- Let's put on coats and go together.
- Okay, okay. Bring it.

1578
01:21:42,470 --> 01:21:45,980
My coat is over there.

1579
01:21:47,230 --> 01:21:50,100
- This is for the better.
- Seriously.

1580
01:21:51,050 --> 01:21:53,140
Gosh, seriously.

1581
01:21:53,140 --> 01:21:56,370
You don't have to be like that.

1582
01:21:56,370 --> 01:21:58,010
It's okay.

1583
01:21:58,010 --> 01:22:00,710
It's because I cooked too much.

1584
01:22:00,710 --> 01:22:02,760
That's not true.

1585
01:22:04,140 --> 01:22:05,400
Get a hold of yourself.

1586
01:22:05,400 --> 01:22:06,850
But why...

1587
01:22:06,850 --> 01:22:09,760
You'll remember this fondly, too.

1588
01:22:09,760 --> 01:22:11,330
Gosh, seriously.

1589
01:22:11,330 --> 01:22:14,780
How could she not fall for him now?

1590
01:22:16,340 --> 01:22:17,420
[Pale]

1591
01:22:17,420 --> 01:22:19,190
What's that?

1592
01:22:20,290 --> 01:22:22,020
[Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong's first dishes]

1593
01:22:22,020 --> 01:22:23,840
I'm hungry.

1594
01:22:23,840 --> 01:22:25,090
So exciting.

1595
01:22:25,090 --> 01:22:27,860
I've never seen food that looks this bad.

1596
01:22:27,860 --> 01:22:30,310
It's so funny.

1597
01:22:31,220 --> 01:22:32,930
I'm so sorry.

1598
01:22:32,930 --> 01:22:34,540
I'm so happy.

1599
01:22:34,540 --> 01:22:36,220
We'll do better next time.

1600
01:22:36,220 --> 01:22:38,930
It's okay. You worked so hard.

1601
01:22:38,930 --> 01:22:42,280
- Thank you for the meal.
- Thank you.

1602
01:22:42,280 --> 01:22:43,990
Thank you for the meal.

1603
01:22:43,990 --> 01:22:46,530
They must be embarrassed.

1604
01:22:49,280 --> 01:22:51,690
Tasting the beef he cooked.

1605
01:22:51,690 --> 01:22:52,760
[Laughing]

1606
01:22:52,760 --> 01:22:54,890
It's cold.

1607
01:22:56,530 --> 01:22:59,160
- Hope you understand.
- I'll be careful.

1608
01:23:01,640 --> 01:23:03,420
[Yum]

1609
01:23:03,420 --> 01:23:05,970
It's cold, but it's tasty.

1610
01:23:05,970 --> 01:23:07,460
Is it?

1611
01:23:08,390 --> 01:23:12,030
I gave up and didn't season it properly.

1612
01:23:14,060 --> 01:23:16,200
[Embarrassed]

1613
01:23:16,200 --> 01:23:18,370
Ah...

1614
01:23:18,370 --> 01:23:19,510
[Sniff]

1615
01:23:19,510 --> 01:23:21,600
He's enjoying it.

1616
01:23:21,600 --> 01:23:23,570
It smells so good.

1617
01:23:24,440 --> 01:23:26,130
It's plenty good.

1618
01:23:26,130 --> 01:23:27,540
[Nodding]

1619
01:23:27,540 --> 01:23:29,040
[Hehe]

1620
01:23:29,700 --> 01:23:32,370
I'm not just saying it. It's good.

1621
01:23:32,370 --> 01:23:35,940
They're pretending, right? It can't be good.

1622
01:23:40,000 --> 01:23:42,530
- It's tasty.
- Tasty?

1623
01:23:43,270 --> 01:23:44,640
[Hehe]

1624
01:23:44,640 --> 01:23:46,490
Wu Yeol seems to know.

1625
01:23:46,490 --> 01:23:49,650
He knew since he was in the kitchen.

1626
01:23:49,650 --> 01:23:51,120
[Laughing]

1627
01:23:54,920 --> 01:23:58,290
[Inhaling]

1628
01:23:58,290 --> 01:24:01,200
He's eating to be nice.

1629
01:24:10,650 --> 01:24:11,860
[Transparent Seo Won]

1630
01:24:11,860 --> 01:24:14,310
- It's too funny.
- He's the funniest.

1631
01:24:14,310 --> 01:24:17,000
Seo Won is the funniest. He is.

1632
01:24:17,000 --> 01:24:19,250
He's winning her over by eating a lot.

1633
01:24:19,250 --> 01:24:21,850
Right, right.

1634
01:24:21,850 --> 01:24:23,270
It's tasty.

1635
01:24:24,180 --> 01:24:26,500
I was so hungry to begin with.

1636
01:24:27,800 --> 01:24:30,470
[Surprised]

1637
01:24:32,510 --> 01:24:34,070
He finished it.

1638
01:24:34,070 --> 01:24:37,860
It's really tasty. So is the mushroom.

1639
01:24:37,860 --> 01:24:40,380
[Scraping]

1640
01:24:40,380 --> 01:24:43,630
He doesn't have to scrape so hard.

1641
01:24:43,630 --> 01:24:47,010
You're eating so much pasta for us.

1642
01:24:47,010 --> 01:24:49,720
It's really tasty. I mean it.

1643
01:24:51,510 --> 01:24:53,640
Did I scrape it too much?

1644
01:24:53,640 --> 01:24:56,570
He is trying to win her over.

1645
01:24:57,890 --> 01:25:00,780
[Yum]

1646
01:25:00,780 --> 01:25:02,420
[Smile]

1647
01:25:04,890 --> 01:25:06,670
[Yum]

1648
01:25:10,030 --> 01:25:13,250
It was objectively inedible.

1649
01:25:13,250 --> 01:25:15,580
[Fact attack]

1650
01:25:15,890 --> 01:25:17,890
[Brutal review]

1651
01:25:17,890 --> 01:25:21,110
I love her. She's so honest.

1652
01:25:21,110 --> 01:25:23,380
You have to be objective, for sure.

1653
01:25:23,380 --> 01:25:27,060
He's letting everyone know.
It was objectively bad.

1654
01:25:27,060 --> 01:25:30,080
It was objectively inedible.

1655
01:25:30,080 --> 01:25:31,960
I'm sorry to say.

1656
01:25:31,960 --> 01:25:34,870
You had to force yourself to eat it.

1657
01:25:34,870 --> 01:25:37,180
But he was scraping the bowl.

1658
01:25:37,180 --> 01:25:39,280
He was trying so hard.

1659
01:25:39,280 --> 01:25:42,090
He must like Yu Gyeong a lot.

1660
01:25:42,090 --> 01:25:43,250
He's all in.

1661
01:25:43,250 --> 01:25:44,970
Isn't there more pasta left?

1662
01:25:44,970 --> 01:25:46,600
There is.

1663
01:25:47,530 --> 01:25:49,020
[Pausing]

1664
01:25:49,020 --> 01:25:51,200
- There is a lot.
- No, it's not that.

1665
01:25:51,200 --> 01:25:53,490
[Laughing]

1666
01:26:01,550 --> 01:26:03,100
[Checking]

1667
01:26:05,810 --> 01:26:07,060
It's hard.

1668
01:26:07,060 --> 01:26:10,290
Of all dinners on Heart Signal,

1669
01:26:10,290 --> 01:26:12,770
this was the worst one.

1670
01:26:12,770 --> 01:26:15,190
- Never seen this.
- It was a failure.

1671
01:26:15,190 --> 01:26:18,970
This failure reveals their characters.

1672
01:26:18,970 --> 01:26:21,300
The kitchen is everything on Heart Signal.

1673
01:26:21,300 --> 01:26:22,440
It was great.

1674
01:26:22,440 --> 01:26:25,130
In Heart Signal's history,

1675
01:26:25,130 --> 01:26:28,060
Yu Gyeong's wall crumbled the quickest.

1676
01:26:28,100 --> 01:26:31,200
She built the wall to dismantle it.

1677
01:26:31,210 --> 01:26:33,480
Did you see her at the sink?

1678
01:26:33,480 --> 01:26:36,090
"I'm happy. No, I can't be happy."

1679
01:26:36,090 --> 01:26:38,120
You could see that in that moment.

1680
01:26:38,120 --> 01:26:39,720
She was so happy

1681
01:26:39,720 --> 01:26:42,240
until the unwelcome guests appeared.

1682
01:26:42,240 --> 01:26:45,690
Yu Gyeong felt uncomfortable when everyone came.

1683
01:26:45,700 --> 01:26:48,480
She couldn't hide it. But Wu Yeol was so calm.

1684
01:26:48,480 --> 01:26:50,370
He must've been calm...

1685
01:26:50,370 --> 01:26:53,520
because he knew Yu Gyeong was into him.

1686
01:26:53,520 --> 01:26:55,520
Right, right.

1687
01:26:55,520 --> 01:26:58,550
And thanks to Seo Won,

1688
01:26:58,550 --> 01:27:02,170
who was way too nosy,

1689
01:27:02,170 --> 01:27:05,280
she must've felt for Wu Yeol more.

1690
01:27:05,280 --> 01:27:06,460
Right, right.

1691
01:27:06,460 --> 01:27:09,020
He even put on an apron.

1692
01:27:09,020 --> 01:27:10,240
It's too much.

1693
01:27:10,240 --> 01:27:13,750
He was sabotaging on the first day.

1694
01:27:13,750 --> 01:27:15,720
Sabotage?

1695
01:27:15,720 --> 01:27:20,130
It's sad that liking someone means sabotaging.

1696
01:27:20,130 --> 01:27:22,960
Up to Season 4, people had manners.

1697
01:27:22,960 --> 01:27:24,440
They have no manners.

1698
01:27:24,440 --> 01:27:26,710
They used to take a bite and leave.

1699
01:27:26,710 --> 01:27:28,360
But he just barged in.

1700
01:27:28,360 --> 01:27:30,560
He basically pushed himself in there.

1701
01:27:30,560 --> 01:27:33,360
He doesn't care that there's someone else.

1702
01:27:33,360 --> 01:27:35,400
He's like a bulldozer.

1703
01:27:35,400 --> 01:27:39,060
If someone comes over, you chat with them.

1704
01:27:39,100 --> 01:27:42,200
But they had their backs on them. The two men.

1705
01:27:42,200 --> 01:27:43,560
They couldn't even hear them.

1706
01:27:43,560 --> 01:27:48,570
When men are attracted to a woman,
they become like this.

1707
01:27:48,570 --> 01:27:50,680
They seemed so sad and lost.

1708
01:27:50,680 --> 01:27:54,810
You know why? They dolled up
before they came down.

1709
01:27:54,810 --> 01:27:57,640
- Right.
- Showing off her shoulder, too.

1710
01:27:57,640 --> 01:27:59,460
But they only saw the men's backs.

1711
01:27:59,460 --> 01:28:02,460
And their questions were ignored.

1712
01:28:02,460 --> 01:28:06,960
This is the first day.
What will they do the next day?

1713
01:28:07,000 --> 01:28:11,280
I think the jealousy will either make them

1714
01:28:11,280 --> 01:28:14,840
want to possess, or they'll let them go.

1715
01:28:14,840 --> 01:28:17,200
I think it will be the former.

1716
01:28:17,200 --> 01:28:20,380
Seo Won has been doing that in the kitchen,

1717
01:28:20,380 --> 01:28:22,950
but she kept trying.

1718
01:28:22,950 --> 01:28:26,160
She has a fighting spirit.

1719
01:28:26,160 --> 01:28:27,760
She's on the move.

1720
01:28:27,760 --> 01:28:29,210
She gets provoked quickly.

1721
01:28:29,210 --> 01:28:31,020
They need to change starting tomorrow.

1722
01:28:31,020 --> 01:28:33,070
I'm really loving this.

1723
01:28:33,070 --> 01:28:34,860
Shall we raise glasses?

1724
01:28:34,860 --> 01:28:37,180
Good work.

1725
01:28:37,180 --> 01:28:39,860
[Celebrating their beginning]

1726
01:28:45,480 --> 01:28:46,840
[Sigh]

1727
01:28:47,320 --> 01:28:48,420
[Sigh]

1728
01:28:48,420 --> 01:28:49,950
Nice.

1729
01:28:49,950 --> 01:28:52,540
[The day went by quickly]

1730
01:28:52,540 --> 01:28:56,310
Today felt very long,

1731
01:28:56,310 --> 01:28:59,380
but it's already 11:30 now. It felt short, too.

1732
01:28:59,380 --> 01:29:02,000
Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong are sitting together.

1733
01:29:02,000 --> 01:29:03,910
I'm kind of sad.

1734
01:29:05,300 --> 01:29:08,280
Should we guess our ages?

1735
01:29:08,280 --> 01:29:10,400
Which man looks the youngest?

1736
01:29:10,400 --> 01:29:13,410
That would be less hurtful, right?

1737
01:29:13,410 --> 01:29:14,550
That sounds fun.

1738
01:29:14,550 --> 01:29:16,060
[Looking around]

1739
01:29:16,060 --> 01:29:18,550
I think he's the youngest.

1740
01:29:18,550 --> 01:29:20,550
- Me?
- Yes.

1741
01:29:26,720 --> 01:29:29,740
- Why?
- When you first came,

1742
01:29:29,740 --> 01:29:31,850
I didn't think so.

1743
01:29:31,850 --> 01:29:36,510
But his smile and stuff emit a young vibe.

1744
01:29:36,510 --> 01:29:38,970
He seems young.

1745
01:29:38,970 --> 01:29:40,300
Don't you think? When he smiles.

1746
01:29:40,300 --> 01:29:43,950
He looks a bit cold when he doesn't.

1747
01:29:43,950 --> 01:29:45,990
But when he smiles, he looks young.

1748
01:29:45,990 --> 01:29:48,950
- I think he's the youngest.
- Right. When he smiles.

1749
01:29:48,950 --> 01:29:51,750
- He doesn't look happy.
- He's upset.

1750
01:29:52,780 --> 01:29:55,020
Should we move on?

1751
01:29:55,020 --> 01:29:58,940
[While they were discussing age]

1752
01:29:58,940 --> 01:29:59,910
It's here.

1753
01:29:59,910 --> 01:30:04,110
- It's message time.
- Here it is. Here it is.

1754
01:30:04,110 --> 01:30:09,680
[Who is your heart headed to?]

1755
01:30:10,490 --> 01:30:15,390
[Express your feelings through a text]

1756
01:30:15,910 --> 01:30:20,340
[Feeling conflicted by a text]

1757
01:30:21,970 --> 01:30:26,210
[Who will they text on the first night?]

1758
01:30:26,210 --> 01:30:30,970
[Did you detect their heart signals?]

1759
01:30:30,970 --> 01:30:34,490
From this moment, predictors can predict

1760
01:30:34,490 --> 01:30:37,620
the six people's love lines based on clues.

1761
01:30:37,620 --> 01:30:39,690
- This is hard.
- I know.

1762
01:30:39,690 --> 01:30:42,130
The first quiz is finally here.

1763
01:30:42,130 --> 01:30:44,170
It's nerve-racking since it's been three years.

1764
01:30:44,170 --> 01:30:50,060
Each night, the tenants will text
one person they're attracted to.

1765
01:30:50,060 --> 01:30:53,930
The text will be sent under nicknames.

1766
01:30:53,930 --> 01:30:57,180
They can't reveal the nicknames
until the reveal day.

1767
01:30:57,180 --> 01:30:59,230
They have consistent nicknames?

1768
01:30:59,230 --> 01:31:00,500
They do.

1769
01:31:00,550 --> 01:31:01,930
- But no one knows who's who.
- They don't know.

1770
01:31:01,930 --> 01:31:02,860
They don't know.

1771
01:31:02,860 --> 01:31:04,860
So exciting.

1772
01:31:04,860 --> 01:31:06,930
Today's quiz is a group quiz.

1773
01:31:06,930 --> 01:31:08,950
Let's start with the easiest one.

1774
01:31:08,950 --> 01:31:11,080
The easiest one is Kim Seo Won, right?

1775
01:31:11,080 --> 01:31:13,160
Of course.

1776
01:31:13,160 --> 01:31:15,080
Kim Seo Won will choose Kang Yu Gyeong.

1777
01:31:15,080 --> 01:31:16,610
Yes, of course.

1778
01:31:16,610 --> 01:31:18,440
You don't have to reveal the answer.

1779
01:31:18,440 --> 01:31:20,020
Speaking of Kang Yu Gyeong...

1780
01:31:20,020 --> 01:31:22,610
She'll choose Park Wu Yeol.

1781
01:31:22,610 --> 01:31:26,030
She must've texted him
since they worked together.

1782
01:31:26,030 --> 01:31:30,030
I think Gyu Ri chose Seo Won.

1783
01:31:30,100 --> 01:31:32,900
- She kept talking to him, too.
- I agree.

1784
01:31:32,900 --> 01:31:35,950
Even after seeing him slurping the pasta.

1785
01:31:35,950 --> 01:31:38,500
Since she's a bit jealous now,

1786
01:31:38,500 --> 01:31:41,980
she'll give it a go, I think.

1787
01:31:41,980 --> 01:31:43,830
Did Gyu Ri choose Wu Yeol?

1788
01:31:43,830 --> 01:31:46,310
Because he was so kind to her?

1789
01:31:46,310 --> 01:31:48,800
She's been hurt and... That's it.

1790
01:31:48,800 --> 01:31:51,040
He offered her a ride, too.

1791
01:31:51,040 --> 01:31:53,420
He was going the opposite way, too.

1792
01:31:53,420 --> 01:31:56,020
That might've moved Gyu Ri.

1793
01:31:56,100 --> 01:32:01,100
She got hurt by Seo Won,
and Wu Yeol was kind to her.

1794
01:32:01,110 --> 01:32:03,040
I think Gyu Ri will choose Wu Yeol.

1795
01:32:03,040 --> 01:32:04,430
Seong Min.

1796
01:32:04,430 --> 01:32:05,750
Seong Min will choose Yu Gyeong.

1797
01:32:05,750 --> 01:32:07,240
Seong Min chooses Yu Gyeong?

1798
01:32:07,240 --> 01:32:09,780
- Why not Yu Gyeong?
- He came over to help.

1799
01:32:09,780 --> 01:32:12,070
He turned his back on the other two.

1800
01:32:12,070 --> 01:32:14,190
He can't do that to someone he likes.

1801
01:32:14,190 --> 01:32:16,430
I agree. You're right.

1802
01:32:16,430 --> 01:32:18,300
- You're right.
- You agree.

1803
01:32:18,300 --> 01:32:20,370
And Min Ju.

1804
01:32:20,370 --> 01:32:22,120
- Seong Min.
- I agree.

1805
01:32:22,120 --> 01:32:25,090
She had a smooth conversation with him.

1806
01:32:25,090 --> 01:32:27,250
Park Wu Yeol is the only one left.

1807
01:32:27,250 --> 01:32:29,450
I can't tell with Wu Yeol.

1808
01:32:29,450 --> 01:32:31,480
I say he chooses Kang Yu Gyeong.

1809
01:32:31,480 --> 01:32:33,580
I chose her, too.

1810
01:32:33,580 --> 01:32:35,690
Yu Gyeong. All Yu Gyeong?

1811
01:32:35,690 --> 01:32:36,850
I think it's Gyu Ri.

1812
01:32:36,850 --> 01:32:39,180
All Kang Yu Gyeong or Gyu Ri?

1813
01:32:39,180 --> 01:32:41,340
You need to remember the beginning.

1814
01:32:41,340 --> 01:32:44,780
His ears turned red only for Gyu Ri.

1815
01:32:44,780 --> 01:32:51,120
He should've let her taste the beef
while cooking it, then.

1816
01:32:51,120 --> 01:32:55,200
But it was his first time cooking.

1817
01:32:55,200 --> 01:32:56,860
He couldn't focus on anything else.

1818
01:32:56,860 --> 01:32:58,860
He was cutting raw beef with scissors.

1819
01:32:58,860 --> 01:33:00,340
He offered her a ride.

1820
01:33:00,340 --> 01:33:04,100
When cooking, rather than
showing interest in Gyu Ri,

1821
01:33:04,100 --> 01:33:07,410
he focused on Yu Gyeong, who was frustrated.

1822
01:33:07,410 --> 01:33:09,330
In the end, when they drank...

1823
01:33:09,330 --> 01:33:12,340
- I know.
- He was smiling at her the whole time.

1824
01:33:12,340 --> 01:33:15,620
He kept smiling at her, sitting next to her.

1825
01:33:15,620 --> 01:33:17,300
They were sitting closely.

1826
01:33:17,300 --> 01:33:21,980
Statistically, one person gets
all the votes on Day 1.

1827
01:33:21,980 --> 01:33:24,320
I think that's right.

1828
01:33:24,320 --> 01:33:26,550
You keep waffling.

1829
01:33:26,550 --> 01:33:28,070
You have thin ears.

1830
01:33:28,070 --> 01:33:31,290
Gyu Ri and Wu Yeol are so hard.

1831
01:33:31,300 --> 01:33:36,900
He likes Gyu Ri, but Yu Gyeong
went through a lot that day.

1832
01:33:36,900 --> 01:33:38,430
I think Wu Yeol will choose Gyu Ri.

1833
01:33:38,430 --> 01:33:42,090
I almost got persuaded by Sang Min.

1834
01:33:42,090 --> 01:33:45,770
All men were flocking around Yu Gyeong.

1835
01:33:45,770 --> 01:33:49,480
I don't think he wants to be one of them yet.

1836
01:33:49,480 --> 01:33:52,900
I don't think he likes her that much yet.

1837
01:33:55,050 --> 01:33:58,000
Hearing Roy, I think it's Yu Gyeong now.

1838
01:33:58,000 --> 01:33:59,620
My vote was for Gyu Ri.

1839
01:33:59,620 --> 01:34:00,830
Let's go with Gyu Ri.

1840
01:34:00,830 --> 01:34:02,690
He likes Yu Gyeong,

1841
01:34:02,690 --> 01:34:06,060
but she doesn't make him nervous yet.

1842
01:34:06,060 --> 01:34:09,650
Since the waffling Roy is so sure,

1843
01:34:09,650 --> 01:34:12,750
I think it might be the opposite.

1844
01:34:12,750 --> 01:34:14,230
I think it's Yu Gyeong now.

1845
01:34:14,230 --> 01:34:16,530
Let's still listen to Roy.

1846
01:34:16,530 --> 01:34:17,920
- Okay.
- Got it.

1847
01:34:17,920 --> 01:34:20,340
Regardless of what we saw today,

1848
01:34:20,340 --> 01:34:24,630
we'll see if Roy Kim is poop or gold.

1849
01:34:24,630 --> 01:34:26,390
It's determined in Episode 1?

1850
01:34:26,390 --> 01:34:31,690
Let's see what his contribution brings us.

1851
01:34:31,690 --> 01:34:33,960
Connect Wu Yeol to Gyu Ri.

1852
01:34:35,790 --> 01:34:37,860
[Please...]

1853
01:34:37,860 --> 01:34:40,980
In Heart Signal 5, we only get the nicknames.

1854
01:34:40,980 --> 01:34:43,460
Okay, okay. Understood.

1855
01:34:43,460 --> 01:34:46,600
[It's getting late at Signal House]

1856
01:34:47,000 --> 01:34:48,470
[Clanking]

1857
01:34:49,780 --> 01:34:51,360
[Pouring]

1858
01:34:56,630 --> 01:35:00,280
[Looking back on the short but long day]

1859
01:35:00,910 --> 01:35:03,050
Do I really look the youngest?

1860
01:35:03,050 --> 01:35:06,110
When you smile, you look so young.

1861
01:35:06,110 --> 01:35:10,010
I thought you were the oldest at first.

1862
01:35:10,010 --> 01:35:13,240
That's what I thought at first.

1863
01:35:13,240 --> 01:35:15,250
But you smile so brightly.

1864
01:35:15,250 --> 01:35:19,070
The smile seemed so young to me.

1865
01:35:19,070 --> 01:35:21,800
I thought it was so charming.

1866
01:35:22,790 --> 01:35:24,500
[Seo Won is keeping a diary]

1867
01:35:24,500 --> 01:35:28,400
I was going to bring it, but I didn't.

1868
01:35:28,420 --> 01:35:30,150
Do you want paper?

1869
01:35:31,520 --> 01:35:33,620
I'll just borrow the pencil later.

1870
01:35:33,620 --> 01:35:35,600
[While the male tenants are building friendship]

1871
01:35:35,600 --> 01:35:37,470
Seriously. What do we do?

1872
01:35:37,470 --> 01:35:38,800
[The women's room]

1873
01:35:39,150 --> 01:35:41,400
[Pondering]

1874
01:35:41,910 --> 01:35:45,450
You do get...

1875
01:35:46,900 --> 01:35:50,200
- hung up on the text.
- Of course.

1876
01:35:50,210 --> 01:35:52,580
I might have a lot of thoughts,

1877
01:35:52,580 --> 01:35:57,180
but I only get to text one person.

1878
01:35:58,580 --> 01:36:01,620
[Who do they text after thinking hard?]

1879
01:36:06,620 --> 01:36:09,100
